  "body": "\nA note on how to use Morisawa's BIZ UD font, which was made available under the SIL license on 3/20/20/2022.\n\n[Morisawa offers BIZ UD Font, a universal design friendly font, to Google Fonts](https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000287.000010848.html)\n\n```python\nfrom PIL import ImageFont\nfrom urllib.request import urlopen\n\nfont = ImageFont.truetype(\n    urlopen(\"https://github.com/googlefonts/morisawa-biz-ud-mincho/raw/main/fonts/ttf/BIZUDPMincho-Regular.ttf\")\n)\n```\n\nReading TrueTypeFont normally refers to the `.ttf` file of the host OS, but since it is possible to specify the bytes type, `urlopen` is used to refer to the file on github.\n\nThis eliminates dependence on the font status of the host OS and allows stress- free image generation.\n\n- - - \n\nI no longer have to think about what to do with fonts with GitHub Actions, so it's so much easier!",
